programme.title: Louisiana Catch and Cook
programme.desc:
In this episode, Chef Jay Ducote brings along a very special fishing buddy, his dad, for our first-ever Catch & Cook freshwater adventure! We’re heading to the legendary Toledo Bend, famous for its sac-a-lait (Cajun for crappie) and ranked among the top bass lakes in the U.S. It’s a bucket-list stop for anglers everywhere, but trust us, the story doesn’t end with the fish.
Steeped in Spanish, French, and Native American roots dating back to the Louisiana Purchase, this region serves up culture and flavor as rich as its fishing. We’ll be staying at Wildwood Resort, hitting the water with Captain Matt Loetscher of Living The Dream Guide Service, and capping off the day with spectacular lake views from their breezy lakeside bar. Hook, line, and sinker — you don’t want to miss this one!
Ready to go catchin’ with one of Louisiana’s best captains? Visit www.LouisianaCharterFishing.com to check availability or book your trip today!

programme.title: Louisiana Catch and Cook
programme.desc:
In this episode we’re headed down to the fishing village of Shell Beach in St. Bernard Parish for a full Louisiana experience! Joining us is Chef Lynnae Oxley, a chef from the Pacific Northwest who once beat our own Jay Ducote on Food Network’s Chopped. On the way, we make a pit stop at the iconic Abita Brewery on Tchoupitoulas in New Orleans, then grab lunch and cook up some classic hog’s head cheese at Jeanfreau’s Meat Market. From there, it’s all about the water — trout and redfish with Captain Don, crawfish and crabs with Captain Sal, followed by the ultimate Louisiana feast as we cook up our fresh catch at the Gotcha Hooked Lodge’s outdoor kitchen. It’s fishing, food, and culture — served up Bayou style!
Ready to go catchin’ with one of Louisiana’s best captains? Visit www.LouisianaCharterFishing.com to check availability or book your trip today!

programme.title: Iowa Giant At The Buzzer, Justin And Drake's Epic Hunting Season
programme.desc: On this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail, we kick things off with Mike Reed who wastes no time getting back out to the River Farm following the close of Iowa's deer season. With the goal of keeping tabs on the deer herd and also providing them with excellent nutrition moving forward into the coldest months of the year, Mike gets his Ax One Complete Feed from our good friends at @axoutdoors7116 out on multiple locations on the farm and discusses the benefit that the product can yield for you. From there, we join Justin Karns who takes us along for the journey of his epic 2024 deer season with partner in crime Drake Lamb. Together, the duo logged big buck encounter after big buck encounter that included a once in a lifetime close range sighting of an Iowa monarch locked down with a doe and a giant up and comer on Justin's treasured home farm. Utilizing one of many food plots implemented at the home farm, the encounter encapsulated years of hard work improving the ground his family calls home. Down to the final days of season, the guys pushed forward and showed that the grind always pays off with Justin tagging a great buck and rounding out an incredible 2024 deer hunting journey. As always, we thank you for joining us on another episode of Midwest Whitetail and we hope you enjoy the show!

programme.title: Surprise Giant 8 Hits The Ground, First Buck Of 2025
programme.desc: On this week's episode we are back in Iowa kicking off 2025 in a big way. After less than stellar weather all shotgun season, frigid cold has graced the Midwest prompting some great hunting. Heading back to the bottom plot, Mike and Bella Reed are hoping to finally lay eyes on an ancient buck known as "Anna's Buck." Right away, a giant surprise buck hits the field well before legal shooting time when the duo notice something is off. Carrying a major leg injury, Bella makes a perfect shot on the giant 8 and fills a second tag by the time the evening ends. Putting the stamp on her greatest season yet, we couldn't be happier for her and look forward to seeing what the rest of the late season has in store. As always, thanks for watching another episode of Midwest Whitetail!

programme.title: 2nd Big Buck Down Of The Season, How We're Hunting The Last 11 Days
programme.desc: Welcome back to another week of Midwest Whitetail. From all of us on the team we sincerely hope you enjoyed a great Christmas holiday with loved ones, and if you got out in the woods, had some luck punching a tag! On this episode, we join a few of the guys who take us through a multitude of proven and time-sensitive strategies with the final days of season in front of us. First up to bat is Mike Reed who has been hitting the field hard with the Reed family hoping to cash in on the hard work put in all off season long. With multiple targets at the top of the list, Mike and the crew are hopeful that a timely incoming cold front will be the ticket in punching their tags. Next, Owen Reigler is back with another update on the cat and mouse game he has played with the buck he calls "The Enforcer" all season long. Owen also dives into various great tips for hunting in a tree stand during the late season as well as keys to accessing and exiting your hunting spots to ensure they stay fresh hunt after hunt. Then, Zach Rozmus is back in action from sitting the sidelines after tagging out in November. Sitting the same area that saw him tag the giant he called T-Bone the prior year, Zach has news of a new potential target that may find itself at the top of his Hitlist for the remaining days of season. Finally, team member Collins Marine and better half Elizabeth Splinter return to Collins' main river bottom farm that Elizabeth found success on back in early November. Sitting a tried and true Redneck blind overlooking a MonsterBuck greens plot, the duo find themselves behind yet another great buck and add another tag punched to a banner year for the entire family.

programme.title: Like a Train
programme.desc: The Knights continue down the path to victory. Their journey must include team growth and bonding. Friendships and trust develop as the team goes through hardships such as injuries and new players. Along the way, we learn more about them, why they work so well together, whom they've lost, and how they've charged forth in spite of it all. Oh, and there's rain, lots of rain. Meet the team and hear their stories. They will excite you, move you and make you think about things you didn’t expect out of a sports documentary. Its original score, also composed and performed by the students, will have you tapping your feet as you root for the Knights.

programme.title: Real Man TV
programme.desc: In the last episode, Kyle took to the skies; now it’s the seas. Co-host Josh Peterson joins Kyle on a deep sea fishing excursion that ends in one of them losing their lunch.. but who will it be? Later (after everyone’s cleaned up) the gang reconvenes for a legendary course of fire with some serious artillery.. and Bob.

programme.title: The Big Reveal
programme.desc: The Big Reveal does it again by bringing three very different entrepreneurs together, all connected by their pioneer spirit. Flag Guard tips off this episode by explaining how they’re doing their part in keeping your loved ones safe. After that, Dr. West explains how his revolutionary probiotic will fix your digestive health 100% of the time. Host Kevin Harrington then caps off this episode in style with a trip to Tommasina Eyewear’s studio with a peak behind the curtain.

programme.title: All Stars
programme.desc: With physical training underway, Don hands the All Stars to master weaponry specialists for intense combat preparation. The contestants face a grueling course of fire with a high-powered rifle, alongside fire-making and blade training challenges. Pushed to their limits, they race to earn points for the upcoming mission, where every skill counts. Can their new tactics withstand Don Mann’s ultimate test of resilience? Watch to find out in Surviving Mann: All Stars.

programme.title: All Stars
programme.desc: The day kicks off with “The 1000-Yard Shot,” and the All-Stars are put to the test bright and early. Who will “make impact” and who will fall flat? Following the competition, Don receives a call from the CIA: the mission is officially greenlit, and it’s time for the All-Stars to kick things into high gear. This moment marks a pivotal shift in their training, with lives now hanging in the balance. After a crash course in the classroom, the All-Stars head to the field for what they think is a land navigation exercise… but things quickly spiral when a group of aggressive hostiles ambushes and captures the competitors for an intense hostage training scenario. Will any of them make it out—and live to tell the tale?

When the amount of drug trafficking is uncovered, it's a wakeup call for the community and the students themselves.
